position, as in Ragger,M-Rapport,R, Rapport-Ragger Match Szombathely HUN 2011
1-0 (71)}) (11... Bg4 {is actually a good move, played in 1-0 Bacrot,E-Nanu,C
TCh-FRA Top 12 2012 1-0 (39). Now instead of swaping the bishops, more
promising is} 12. f3 {[%csl Rg4]} Bc8 13. a4 $14 {[%csl Rb5,Ge4,Rg5][%cal
Gg5e4] and white does not have to fear for his knight as it has a comfortable
base on e4.}) 12. e4 Bg4 ({Kamsky's latest try was materialistic, but risky} 
12... hxg5 13. exf5 gxf5 14. Bxg5 Qxd4 {[%csl Rg8][%cal Gg3g8,Gh3h8] You may
remember that we analyzed a similar position in the Repertoire against the
