whose kingisde is wide open. Ramirez conducted the game well} 15. Rad1 Qc5 16.
Rc1 Qa7 17. Qb4 e6 18. Qh4 Nbd7 {0-1 Ramirez,A (2583)-Kamsky,G (2712)/Las
Vegas 2014/CBM 160 Extra} {until this point. Now simple} 19. Rfd1 $40 {[%cal
Gd1d3,Gd3h3] would put black under tremendous pressure.}) 13. Bxg4 hxg5 ({
Another attempt is} 13... Nxg4 14. Nf3 e5 {but it fails to suffice due to} 15.
Nxe5 $1 (15. dxe5 {is imprecise because of} Nd7 $1 16. e6 Nc5 17. exf7+ Rxf7
18. Qc2 Qd3 $44 {with excellent compensation for the pawn.}) 15... Nxe5 16.
dxe5 Bxe5 17. Rd1 ({just not} 17. Bxh6 $4 Qh4 $19) 17... Qh4 18. g3 Qh3 19. Ne2
{and black decided to give a pawn to complete development} Nd7 20. Bxh6 $1 $16
{but he did not survive in: 1-0 Hammer,J (2651)-Burmakin,V (2581)/Fagernes
2015/CBM 165 Extra (28)}) {In this critical position, we have an important
improvement:} 14. Qd1 $1 $146 ({White did not get much after} 14. Be2 Qxd4 15.
Bxg5 Nxe4 16. Nxe4 Qxe4 17. Rae1 e6 18. Bf3 Qf5 19. h4 Nd7 20. Qd1 Ne5 21. Be4
Qg4 22. Qxg4 Nxg4 23. Bxc6 Rac8 $11 {1/2-1/2 Lou,Y (2484)-Kamsky,G (2741)/
